main event: Around 30 civilian witnesses observed approximately 31 bright, hovering objects that moved west and north over Middletown, Ohio on October 4, 1966.
interesting points: The objects appeared to be larger than stars and as bright as light bulbs.
The objects were observed for around 30 minutes before they moved away.
Contact was made with Air Force Operations, but no known aircraft were in the area at the time.
The description of the objects did not fit the normal pattern of aircraft or birds.
One witness described the objects as hazy, indistinct lights or luminous objects that were brighter than stars and moved slowly at low altitude.
